What did we create?

This section provides a more in-depth look at the game development process outlined in the previous section. As exciting as the previous section!

Metroid (Unity Remaster)

We used unity, a cross-platform game engine used to develop 2D and 3D video games, to make our own "Metroid". ChatGPT was an excellent resource for our team to gain familiarity with Unity.

I playtested the original NES "Metroid" and provided suggestions on the desired gameplay outcomes for our "Metroid" game, such as state transitions and the conditions for Samus's animation.

I re-implemented the enemies in "Metroid" and their interactions with Samus, including Samus's damage aesthetics and the unique behaviors of enemies when damaged.

I created the majority of the animations in "Metroid" and some sound effects utilizing the sound system designed by my teammate.

I focused on specific map tiles to increase the realism of the game, such as lava, vertical/horizontal pipes, grass fields, etc.

I designed multiple interfaces, including the static class Utils.

I designed the final room of the customized level.

Signy Adventuryy

We used unity, a cross-platform game engine used to develop 2D and 3D video games, to make Signy Adventuryy. ChatGPT was an excellent resource for our team to gain familiarity with Unity.

I designed the save system for the entire game, allowing the game state to be preserved even after the player quits, and ensuring that some enemies remain dead permanently after being killed.

I designed the room system, which included setting up camera "boundaries" for each room, background switching and enemy respawning (enemy respawning drafted by Yi He) after switching rooms.

I implemented the spike traps, including the effect of teleporting Signy to a safe place after Signy is hurt by a spike.

I rebuilt our NPC system by fixing all the bugs in it and making it support scrolling of pictures and animations.

I programmed the entire game menu (except the background music and the leafy effect).

I implemented all merchants in the game (including their dialogues).

I designed multiple interfaces, including the static class Utils.

I finalized our camera system by fixing all of its bugs.

I implemented black screen fade-in and fade-out effects.

I have drawn some of Signy's sprites.

...more to add after my final exam.
